    {
      "id": "aQfXfPH2y0rGuiV5ReS5b",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 112,
      "y": 205.83334350585938,
      "width": 1272.8990478515625,
      "height": 625,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a1",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 421812324,
      "version": 1547,
      "versionNonce": 1054272805,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782761858261,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Tables\n\n2. Views  --> Virtual Table, its is custom table created -- for viewing purpose -- with coloumns from differnt table.\n    --> you can save a qurey in DB as View object.\n    @DATABASE NOTES 2Q\n\n3. Functions  --> Smallest logical unit created for reusing logic instead of writing it every time.\n    --> (inputs...) -> Function(compute inputs) -> ouputs.\n    --> Functions will not change the state of the database, No Data Modification.Function is only to compute any thing.\n    ---> Functions cannot call stored procedures.\n\n4. Indexes  --> This will help the DB user to retrive data faster.\n    --> I think Index is a datastructure ??\n5. Sequences  --> useful objects that will provide sequence of numbers.\n\n6. Materialized Views  --> you can save a query in DB along with the resulting Data of that query as a Materialized Views Object.\n\n7. Triggers  --> Function that automatically executed onEvent \n\n8. Stored Procedure  --> Father of the Functions. that can also do\n    --> Can Modifiy Databse, so we can use INSERT,UPDATE and DELETE, COMMIT and ROLLBACK.\n    --> can call other stored procedures and functions.\n    @DATABASE NOTES 1Q\n\n9. Packages  --> Contain a collection of Stored Procdeures.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Tables\n\n2. Views  --> Virtual Table, its is custom table created -- for viewing purpose -- with coloumns from differnt table.\n    --> you can save a qurey in DB as View object.\n    @DATABASE NOTES 2Q\n\n3. Functions  --> Smallest logical unit created for reusing logic instead of writing it every time.\n    --> (inputs...) -> Function(compute inputs) -> ouputs.\n    --> Functions will not change the state of the database, No Data Modification.Function is only to compute any thing.\n    ---> Functions cannot call stored procedures.\n\n4. Indexes  --> This will help the DB user to retrive data faster.\n    --> I think Index is a datastructure ??\n5. Sequences  --> useful objects that will provide sequence of numbers.\n\n6. Materialized Views  --> you can save a query in DB along with the resulting Data of that query as a Materialized Views Object.\n\n7. Triggers  --> Function that automatically executed onEvent \n\n8. Stored Procedure  --> Father of the Functions. that can also do\n    --> Can Modifiy Databse, so we can use INSERT,UPDATE and DELETE, COMMIT and ROLLBACK.\n    --> can call other stored procedures and functions.\n    @DATABASE NOTES 1Q\n\n9. Packages  --> Contain a collection of Stored Procdeures.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
